pageContext.claim: “We're winning Michigan by, uh, I'll tell you, I looked at the numbers -- I said, 'Whoa.' I looked, I said, 'Wow, that's a lot.' By almost 300,000 votes, and -- 65% of the vote is in.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump had lost Michigan by a substantial margin — about 155,000 votes, or 2.8 percentage points.
